the baseline regimen. Treatment with i.v. CYC in the induction phase and MMF in 
the maintenance phase and treatment with MMF in the induction phase and a 
reduced dose of the same in the maintenance phase turned out to be a negatively 
dominated regimen.
CONCLUSION: In the Thai context, the combination of i.v. CYC for the induction 
phase followed by AZA for the maintenance phase should be considered as the 
first-line therapy for newly diagnosed severe LN, as it seems to be the most 
cost-saving regimen.

